cs.RO, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on using neuronal circuit policies to control robotic tasks, including the autonomous parking of a real-world rover robot. This makes cs.RO the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a neural information processing system inspired by the structure of the nervous system of the soil-worm, C. elegans. This makes cs.NE a likely sub-category.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper compares the performance of neuronal circuit policies with contemporary deep learning models. This makes cs.LG a likely sub-category.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel approach to learning simple robotic control using neuronal circuit policies. This makes cs.AI a likely sub-category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on using neuronal circuit policies to control real-world robotic systems. This makes cs.SY a possible sub-category.
